msgstr "Monks’ Confession 11"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:0.5"
msgid "11. Bhūtagāmasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on plants"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.34, pts-cs-bu-pc11.1, pts-vp-en.2.226, ms2V_338
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā āḷaviyaṃ viharati aggāḷave cetiye."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Āḷavī at the Aggāḷava Shrine."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āḷavakā bhikkhū navakammaṃ karontā rukkhaṃ chindantipi chedāpentipi."
msgstr "At that time the monks at Āḷavī were doing building work."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.3"
msgid "Aññataropi āḷavako bhikkhu rukkhaṃ chindati."
msgstr "And they cut trees and got them cut."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.4"
msgid "Tasmiṃ rukkhe adhivatthā devatā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Then, when a certain monk was cutting a tree, the deity that lived in it said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.5"
msgid "“mā, bhante, attano bhavanaṃ kattukāmo mayhaṃ bhavanaṃ chindī”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable, don’t cut down our dwelling because you want to build a dwelling for yourself.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.6"
msgid "So bhikkhu anādiyanto chindiyeva, tassā ca devatāya dārakassa bāhuṃ ākoṭesi."
msgstr "Not taking any heed, he just cut it down, and he hurt the arm of that deity’s child."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.7"
msgid "Atha kho tassā devatāya etadahosi—"
msgstr "That deity thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.8"
msgid "“yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ bhikkhuṃ idheva jīvitā voropeyyan”ti."
msgstr "“Perhaps I should just kill this monk?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.9"
msgid "Atha kho tassā devatāya etadahosi—"
msgstr "But then it reconsidered,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.10"
msgid "“na kho metaṃ patirūpaṃ yāhaṃ imaṃ bhikkhuṃ idheva jīvitā voropeyyaṃ."
msgstr "“It wouldn’t be appropriate for me to just kill this monk."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.11"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ bhagavato etamatthaṃ āroceyyan”ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I instead tell the Master about this matter?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.12"
msgid "Atha kho sā devatā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "And it approached the Master"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.13"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "and told him what had happened."

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.14"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, devate."
msgstr "“Well done, deity!"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.15"
msgid "Sādhu kho tvaṃ, devate, taṃ bhikkhuṃ jīvitā na voropesi."
msgstr "It’s good that you didn’t kill that monk."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.16"
msgid "Sacajja tvaṃ, devate, taṃ bhikkhuṃ jīvitā voropeyyāsi, bahuñca tvaṃ, devate, apuññaṃ pasaveyyāsi."
msgstr "If you had killed that monk today, you would have made much demerit."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.17"
msgid "Gaccha tvaṃ, devate, amukasmiṃ okāse rukkho vivitto tasmiṃ upagacchā”ti."
msgstr "The tree over there is empty; take that as your dwelling.”"

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.18"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.19"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā rukkhaṃ chindissantipi chedāpessantipi ekindriyaṃ samaṇā sakyaputtiyā jīvaṃ viheṭhentī”ti."
msgstr "“How can the Sakyan ascetics cut trees and get them cut? They are hurting life with one sense faculty.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_339
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.20"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.21"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.22"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.227
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.23"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āḷavakā bhikkhū rukkhaṃ chindissantipi chedāpessantipī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can those monks at Āḷavī cut trees and get them cut?”…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.24"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, rukkhaṃ chindathāpi chedāpethāpī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.25"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.26"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.27"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, rukkhaṃ chindissathāpi, chedāpessathāpi."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you cut trees and get them cut?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.28"
msgid "Jīvasaññino hi, moghapurisā, manussā rukkhasmiṃ."
msgstr "People regard trees as conscious."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.29"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.30"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.30a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_340
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:1.31"
msgid "“Bhūtagāmapātabyatāya pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk destroys plants, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc4, pts-cs-bu-pc11.2.1, ms2V_341
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.1.1"
msgid "Bhūtagāmo nāma"
msgstr "Plants:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.1.2"
msgid "pañca bījajātāni—"
msgstr "there are five kinds of propagation:"

#. VAR: bījabījameva → bījabījañceva (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.1.3"
msgid "mūlabījaṃ, khandhabījaṃ, phaḷubījaṃ, aggabījaṃ, bījabījameva pañcamaṃ."
msgstr "propagation from roots, propagation from stems, propagation from joints, propagation from cuttings, propagation from seeds."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-pli4.35, ms2V_342
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.1.4"
msgid "Mūlabījaṃ nāma—"
msgstr "Propagation from roots:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.228
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.1.5"
msgid "haliddi, siṅgiveraṃ, vacā, vacattaṃ, ativisā, kaṭukarohiṇī, usīraṃ, bhaddamuttakaṃ, yāni vā panaññānipi atthi mūle jāyanti, mūle sañjāyanti, etaṃ mūlabījaṃ nāma."
msgstr "turmeric, ginger, sweet flag, white orris root, friar’s hood, hellebore, khus-khus, nut grass, or whatever other plants there are that are produced from roots, that grow from roots—this is called “propagation from roots.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_343
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.1.6"
msgid "Khandhabījaṃ nāma—"
msgstr "Propagation from stems:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.1.7"
msgid "assattho, nigrodho, pilakkho, udumbaro, kacchako, kapitthano, yāni vā panaññānipi atthi khandhe jāyanti, khandhe sañjāyanti, etaṃ khandhabījaṃ nāma."
msgstr "the Bodhi tree, the banyan tree, the wave-leaved fig, the cluster fig, the _kacchaka_ fig-tree, the wood-apple tree, or whatever other plants there are that are produced from stems, that grow from stems—this is called “propagation from stems.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_344
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.1.8"
msgid "Phaḷubījaṃ nāma—"
msgstr "Propagation from joints:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.1.9"
msgid "ucchu, veḷu, naḷo, yāni vā panaññānipi atthi pabbe jāyanti, pabbe sañjāyanti, etaṃ phaḷubījaṃ nāma."
msgstr "sugar-cane, bamboo, reed, or whatever other plants there are that are produced from joints, that grow from joints—this is called “propagation from joints.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_345
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.1.10"
msgid "Aggabījaṃ nāma—"
msgstr "Propagation from cuttings:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.229
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.1.11"
msgid "ajjukaṃ, phaṇijjakaṃ, hiriveraṃ, yāni vā panaññānipi atthi agge jāyanti, agge sañjāyanti, etaṃ aggabījaṃ nāma."
msgstr "basil, rosha grass, fragrant swamp mallow, or whatever other plants there are that are produced from cuttings, that grow from cuttings—this is called “propagation from cuttings.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_346
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.1.12"
msgid "Bījabījaṃ nāma—"
msgstr "Propagation from seeds:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.1.13"
msgid "pubbaṇṇaṃ, aparaṇṇaṃ, yāni vā panaññānipi atthi bīje jāyanti, bīje sañjāyanti, etaṃ bījabījaṃ nāma."
msgstr "grains, vegetables, or whatever other plants there are that are produced from seeds, that grow from seeds—this is called “propagation from seeds.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc10, pts-cs-bu-pc11.2.2, ms2V_347
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.2.1"
msgid "Bīje bījasaññī chindati vā chedāpeti vā, bhindati vā bhedāpeti vā, pacati vā pacāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is capable of propagation, and he perceives that it is, and he cuts it or gets it cut, or he breaks it or gets it broken, or he cooks it or gets it cooked, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.2.2"
msgid "Bīje vematiko chindati vā chedāpeti vā, bhindati vā bhedāpeti vā, pacati vā pacāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is capable of propagation, but he is unsure if it is, and he cuts it or gets it cut, or he breaks it or gets it broken, or he cooks it or gets it cooked, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.2.3"
msgid "Bīje abījasaññī chindati vā chedāpeti vā, bhindati vā bhedāpeti vā, pacati vā pacāpeti vā, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is capable of propagation, but he perceives that it is not, and he cuts it or gets it cut, or he breaks it or gets it broken, or he cooks it or gets it cooked, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.2.4"
msgid "Abīje bījasaññī āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not capable of propagation, but he perceives that it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.2.5"
msgid "Abīje vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not capable of propagation, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.2.6"
msgid "Abīje abījasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is not capable of propagation, and he perceives that it is not, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc11, pts-cs-bu-pc11.2.3, ms2V_348
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.3.2"
msgid "“imaṃ jāna, imaṃ dehi, imaṃ āhara, iminā attho, imaṃ kappiyaṃ karohī”ti bhaṇati,     "
msgstr "if he says, “Consider this/give this/bring this/there’s need for this/make this allowable;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.3.3"
msgid "asañcicca,"
msgstr "if it is unintentional;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.3.4"
msgid "assatiyā,"
msgstr "if he is not mindful;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.3.5"
msgid "ajānantassa,"
msgstr "if he does not know;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.3.6"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.3.7"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_349
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc11:2.3.8"
msgid "Bhūtagāmasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The first rule, the training rule on plants, is finished."
